race.comment: TRACEY TARO (2) clocked a fast 29.66 when filling a minor placing over 516m at Dubbo last start. Should be in this for a long way. FEDERAL BULLET (4) is a handy type who notched his 13th career success when too good (29.81) from Box 4 at Wentworth Park. Has a strong record out of this box with three wins and a minor placing from six starts. Leading chance again. FURIOUS (7) looks close to another win after finishing second from Box 2 last time (25.21) at this track. Ran one of the fastest times on the program last start despite finishing in the minors. Expected to feature. RED BALL ROCKET (6) was well backed last start but ran below expectations when seventh (23.05), beaten 7 lengths.
